The Court Orders the Following:  Count #1
Imposed Sentence of:
6 Years Imprisonment (Credit -195 days) Concurrent to Count #2 and case #15CF272
3 Years of Initial Confinement
3 Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Provide DNA sample if not yet provided; 
No contact with with any victim listed in criminal complaint;
Disclose to any physician in writing your drug history/dependency signed by your physician and provide a copy to your Agent. 
Agent to overview or manage any financial transactions, sign any/all releases needed
No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription
Not to work for any financial institution in any capacity
Restitution: Hearing set
Cost: Waived by the Court 
DNA surcharge: Waived by the Court.  
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.  

